result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (8th) [Modifiers: Penalties for Felonies-Class "G" Felony, Requirement for Ignition Interlock Device] and Operating w/ PAC (7th, 8th or 9th) [Modifiers: Penalties for Felonies-Class "G" Felony, Requirement for Ignition Interlock Device]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI (8th) [Modifiers: Penalties for Felonies-Class "G" Felony, Requirement for Ignition Interlock Device] and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (7th, 8th or 9th) [Modifiers: Penalties for Felonies-Class "G" Felony, Requirement for Ignition Interlock Device] was dismissed by the court.

  • Daniel Thomas Hanson was found guilty of OWI (8th) [Modifiers: Penalties for Felonies-Class "G" Felony, Requirement for Ignition Interlock Device], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. supervisions.notes:
-Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.
-Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

-If a Wisconsin State Prison sentence is imposed, outstanding financial obligations shall be paid from all inmate money at a rate of 25% and the balance due as a condition of extended supervision. 

In the event that the defendant is revoked or discharged from either probation or extended supervision with outstanding financial obligations, the supervising agent shall notify the court 10 days prior to the revocation or discharge.  A civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victim(s) and/or governmental entities for any balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect all debt.
